Attribution

The interactive dashboard in web/dashboard/ (and its build source in
tools/dashboard/) is adapted from the MIT-licensed project
"Understand-Anything" by Yuxiang Lin (Lum1104):
  https://github.com/Lum1104/Understand-Anything

Adaptations made for fully-offline, single-egress operation:
  * removed the Google Fonts <link> tags; the same fonts are self-hosted
    locally via @fontsource and bundled at build time (no CDN);
  * removed the shared-link token gate (the 127.0.0.1 bind is the security
    boundary for this local, single-user app);
  * the three core modules it depends on (schema, search, types) are vendored
    as source under tools/dashboard/vendor/core/.
This project (the FastAPI backend, scanner/parser/enrichment pipeline, and the
config/analysis shell) is likewise provided under the MIT License above.
